  "narrative": {
    "intro": "NAICS 541512 (Computer Systems Design Services) shows $18.5B in federal contract obligations for FY2026 to date, across 8,439 awards with an average award size of $2.2M. Obligations are down 41.7% year over year. Recent annual obligations peaked at $33.4B in FY24 and have moved through $31.7B in FY25 to $18.5B in FY26 (fiscal year to date). The FY21–FY26 sequence of annual obligations is $26.7B, $29.9B, $30.5B, $33.4B, $31.7B, and $18.5B. This market remains concentrated among a handful of large federal buyers and prime contractors: the General Services Administration leads buying in FY2026 to date with $3.9B, followed by the Department of Defense with $3.6B and the Department of Veterans Affairs with $2.9B. On the vendor side, ACCENTURE FEDERAL SERVICES LLC holds $1.8B in obligations, followed by GENERAL DYNAMICS INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY, INC. at $1.4B and ORACLE HEALTH GOVERNMENT SERVICES, INC. at $1.3B.",
    "sections": [
