        "body": "Obligations are down 41.7% year over year, with FY2026 to date at $18.5B. Annual obligations for the prior years were $26.7B in FY21, $29.9B in FY22, $30.5B in FY23, $33.4B in FY24, and $31.7B in FY25."
      },
      {
        "heading": "Which agencies and vendors dominate NAICS 541512 in FY2026 to date?",
        "body": "The top buying agencies are led by the General Services Administration with $3.9B, the Department of Defense with $3.6B, and the Department of Veterans Affairs with $2.9B. The top vendors are ACCENTURE FEDERAL SERVICES LLC at $1.8B, GENERAL DYNAMICS INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY, INC. at $1.4B, and ORACLE HEALTH GOVERNMENT SERVICES, INC. at $1.3B."
